<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-12-10T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-12-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="560" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">853.51/303: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-11T00:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">December 11,
                                        1925—midnight</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received December 12—6:15
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>45. Foreign Minister asks to be informed how many Tobacco Bonds are held
                            by Americans, their value in sterling and where deposited. <pb facs="0983" n="887" xml:id="pg_887"/> Have pointedly called his
                            attention to last two sentences Department’s instruction number 6,
                            February 7, 7 p.m., but said I would inquire again by telegraph. Please
                            reply by telegraph.<note n="12" xml:id="d560fn12">The Department
                                referred the Minister to its telegram No. 6, Feb. 7, 1925, 7 p.m.,
                                    <ref target="#pg_883">p. 883</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>